docs/specs/rhei-programs.spec.md:152:When a program exits and has not already advanced the task (via `rhei transition` or `rhei complete`):
docs/specs/rhei-programs.spec.md:154:1. Collect all transitions from the current state that declare an `exit_code` field.
docs/specs/rhei-programs.spec.md:159:6. If no transition matches and exit code is `0`, log a warning: `warning: program exited 0 but task {id} did not advance from '{state}'`.
docs/specs/rhei-programs.spec.md:164:Programs may also call `rhei transition` or `rhei complete` directly via subprocess invocation, just like agents. When a program does so, the task state changes before the program exits, and exit-code evaluation is skipped entirely — the explicit transition takes precedence.
docs/specs/rhei-programs.spec.md:166:If a transition from a program state has no `exit_code` field, it is available for manual invocation (`rhei transition`) or for the program to call directly, but it will never be selected by exit-code evaluation.
docs/specs/rhei-programs.spec.md:168:This allows hybrid approaches where a program handles the common case via exit codes and calls `rhei transition` for edge cases that need more nuanced routing.
